            "title": "30th CUPE local headed to the picket line amid province wide long term care strike",
            "id": "769dff96-5033-40dc-8cf9-981bc91ec63a",
            "description": "More than 100 employees at Lunenburg Home for Special Care in Nova Scotia, represented by Canadian Union of Public Employees (CUPE) Local 4919, have issued a 48-hour notice to strike. They may commence picketing as soon as Saturday, April 25, as part of the ongoing province-wide strike in the long-term care sector. This marks the 30th local chapter to take job action. Christa Sweeney stated, \"We have been eager to return to negotiations since the start of the strike.\"",
